Package model

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    INotification
    This is an interface which sends an email notification detailing the pending/actual outcome of the student's actions when he or she uses the STARS Planner.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AccessTime
    This class holds the start and end date of a student's access period.
    Course
    This class is responsible for modelling a course which details the attributes and methods of each * Course object part of the STARS Planner system.
    EmailNotification
    This is a Singleton class that is responsible for handling the logic of sending notification via E-mail implementing INotification.
    IndexNumber
    This class is responsible for modelling the index number of a course which details the attributes and methods of each IndexNumber object for a particular Course object.
    Lesson
    This class is responsible for modelling a lesson which details the attributes and methods of each Lesson object.
    LoginInfo
    This class is responsible for modelling LoginInfo which details the attributes and methods of each LoginInfo object from a particular user logging into the STARS Planner.
    Storage
    This class is responsible for storing and retrieving all the Student objects and Course objects in the program.
    Student
    This class is responsible for modelling Student which details the attributes and methods of each Student object part of the STARS Planner system.
    TimeTable
    This class is responsible for managing all the index numbers that a particular Student object is registered or in the wait list for.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    AccountType
    Represents the different account types that can access the Stars Application.
    Gender
    This is one of the enum data types we created - Gender The pre-defined group of constants under our Gender data type are: MALE, FEMALE since there are generally 2 types of gender: male and female.
    LessonType
    This is one of the enum data types we created - LessonType The pre-defined group of constants under our Gender data type are: LECTURE, LAB, TUTORIAL since there are generally 3 types of lessons: lecture, lab and tutorial.
    School
    This is one of the enum data types we created - School The pre-defined group of constants under our Gender data type are: SSS, ADM, SCSE In reality, there are obviously more schools in NTU not covered by our programme.
